<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1720,1819]" pageId="7" pageNumber="548">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,446,1720,1748]" pageId="7" pageNumber="548">Taxonomic remarks.</emphasis>
Male genitalia of this species are illustrated in 
<figureCitation box="[980,1097,1721,1747]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="2.[151,203,1273,1300]" captionTargetBox="[299,1294,851,1243]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[292,1295,848,1248]" captionText="FIG. 2. Male genitalia and claws: Ischnomera sicula n.sp., aedeagus (a), apical portion of tegmen (b); I. tenietensis, aedeagus (c), apical portion of tegmen (d); I. xanthoderes, aedeagus (e), apical portion of tegmen (f); I. tenietensis, tarsal claws (h); I. xanthoderes, tarsal claws (g). Figures of both I. xanthoderes and I. tenietensis modified from Svihla (1988)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3469722" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3469722/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="548">Figs. 2e, f</figureCitation>
. The aedeagus is more curved and thicker, differently than in the Maghrebian and the Sicilian species. Tarsal claws are distincly hooked (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1431,1757,1783]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="2.[151,203,1273,1300]" captionTargetBox="[299,1294,851,1243]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[292,1295,848,1248]" captionText="FIG. 2. Male genitalia and claws: Ischnomera sicula n.sp., aedeagus (a), apical portion of tegmen (b); I. tenietensis, aedeagus (c), apical portion of tegmen (d); I. xanthoderes, aedeagus (e), apical portion of tegmen (f); I. tenietensis, tarsal claws (h); I. xanthoderes, tarsal claws (g). Figures of both I. xanthoderes and I. tenietensis modified from Svihla (1988)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3469722" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3469722/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="548">
Figs. 
<quantity box="[1401,1431,1757,1783]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="548" unit="g" value="2.0">2g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,180,1793,1819]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="3.[151,203,788,815]" captionTargetBox="[232,1355,179,762]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[232,1355,179,762]" captionText="FIG. 3. Tarsal claws: Ischnomera sicula n.sp. (a); I. tenietensis (b); I. xanthoderes (c)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3469724" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3469724/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="548">3c</figureCitation>
